%% =================================NOTE 1==================================
%% 								Need more tests
%% =================================NOTE 2==================================
%% Most of the reference values were generated by the DeepSeek AI
%% in the step-by-step reasoning mode. The AI was fed matrices and
%% white points, but not actual algorithms used in this app, so they were
%% calculated by the AI's own algoritms, to avoid using the results of
%% potentially incorrect algorithms as the reference values for testing the
%% same algorithms.
%% Some tests have permssible margins of error somewhat greater than
%% they supposed to be for the 100% ideal reference data, but unfortunatelly
%% AI rounds off intermediate values too often and too early (checked by
%% looking at the AI reasoning and manually recalculating the displayed
%% formulas step by step), so the error in the reference values can be
%% greater than it should be for the "true" reference values, and the
%% calculated values almost always seem more correct.
%% =================================NOTE /==================================

-module(cbet_test).
